race.comment: MATROOSHI (9) was backed off the map at Warrnambool in longer and then came back to this distance, placing at Ballarat. That stacks up, and Meech rides today and will push forward. With average luck, she can go one better. SHOOTER MCGAVIN (2) resumed off placings on the synthetic and charged home from the back to just miss an unlikely win at Ararat. He's much improved and draws low today. Presents fitter and the longer sprint should be right up his alley. JESSUP (3) has raced favourite twice since his easy win at Traralgon at this level. Comes back in grade with a handy 3kg claim and the speedy gelding is sure to give a big sight. HE'S GODSPEED (1) draws awkwardly but won't know himself in a 56. Has Egan aboard today and must be considered.
